Summing the four terms:

$$
T = 4 \left[ (a \cdot b)(c \cdot d) - (a \cdot c)(b \cdot d) + (a \cdot d)(b \cdot c) ight] + 4 \left[ (a \cdot b)(c \cdot d) - (a \cdot d)(b \cdot c) + (a \cdot c)(b \cdot d) ight] + 4 \left[ (a \cdot b)(c \cdot d) - (a \cdot d)(b \cdot c) + (a \cdot c)(b \cdot d) ight] + 4 \left[ (a \cdot b)(c \cdot d) - (a \cdot c)(b \cdot d) + (a \cdot d)(b \cdot c) ight]
$$

Combining coefficients:
- For $(a \cdot b)(c \cdot d)$: $4 + 4 + 4 + 4 = 16$
- For $(a \cdot c)(b \cdot d)$: $-4 + 4 + 4 - 4 = 0$
- For $(a \cdot d)(b \cdot c)$: $4 - 4 - 4 + 4 = 0$
Thus,

$$
T = 16 (a \cdot b)(c \cdot d)
$$


Both methods yield the same result.
